  "prompt": "Which is the best haircut for man?",
  "response": "The \"best\" haircut for a man is highly subjective and depends on several factors, including:\n\n*   **Face shape:** Different haircuts flatter different face shapes.\n*   **Hair type and texture:** The haircut should work with your natural hair.\n*   **Lifestyle:** Consider your daily routine and how much time you want to spend styling your hair.\n*   **Personal style:** The haircut should align with your overall aesthetic and confidence.\n*   **Age:** While not a strict rule, some styles might be more suitable for different age groups.\n\nTo give you more specific advice, I need more information about you.\n*   **Could you describe your face shape?** (Oval, Round, Square, Heart, Oblong, Triangle)\n*   **What is your hair type and texture?** (Straight, Wavy, Curly, Coily; Fine, Medium, Thick)\n*   **How much time do you want to spend styling your hair each day?**\n*   **Are there any hairstyles you particularly like or dislike?**\n*   **Do you have any photos?**\n\nIn the meantime, here are some general categories of popular and versatile haircuts:\n\n*   **Short and Low-Maintenance:**\n    *   **Buzz Cut:** Very short, easy to maintain, and suits many face shapes.\n    *   **Crew Cut:** Slightly longer than a buzz cut, with a subtle taper on the sides.\n    *   **Fade:** Hair gradually gets shorter on the sides and back, blending into the skin. Many variations exist (low fade, mid fade, high fade).\n    *   **Undercut:** Sides and back are buzzed short or faded, with longer hair on top. Versatile for styling.\n\n*   **Medium Length:**\n    *   **Quiff:** Hair is styled upwards and back from the forehead. Requires some styling.\n    *   **Side Part:** Classic and professional, can be styled neatly or more casually.\n    *   **Pompadour:** Similar to a quiff but with more volume and height in the front. Requires more styling.\n    *   **Textured Crop:** Shorter on the sides with some length and texture on top. Good for adding volume and movement.\n    *   **Bro Flow:** Longer hair that's parted in the middle and flows naturally.\n\n*   **Longer Length:**\n    *   **Long and Layered:** Adds movement and texture to longer hair.\n    *   **Man Bun:** Long hair pulled back into a bun.\n    *   **Top Knot:** Similar to a man bun, but with the sides shaved or faded.\n\nOnce you can give me a little more information about your style and lifestyle, I can recommend the best options for you.",
